# 8. いつかきっと、話してほしい

Rui: <You had quite an adventure today, Mizuki...>
Mizuki: <Yeah, but I'm glad we all came back in one piece. I owe you, Rui.>
Rui: <Oh, I didn't do anything.>
Rui: <On the other hand, I never knew you could make that kind of face, Mizuki.>
Mizuki: <What face?>
Rui: <That look of desperation you had on your face when you were looking for help.>
Mizuki: <That's how I looked?! Wipe that from your mind, will you? That was probably the opposite of the cute and fashionable me that you usually see...>
Rui: <Hehe. That may be difficult.>
Rui: <Also, was that girl the one you mentioned to me before? Your "friend"?>
Mizuki: <Maybe. Maybe not...>
Mizuki: <*Sigh*... Anyways, I'm super tired. I'm gonna go to bed now. Bye, Rui.>
Rui: <Good night...>
Rui: <See you at school, Mizuki...>
Mizuki: <Later...>
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (I have to find a way to save Ena and Airi...!)
Mizuki: Did I really look that desperate?
Mizuki: Huh? Ena messaged me...?
Ena: <Thanks for today. Airi, Shizuku and I were thinking about having a group call. Wanna join?>
Mizuki: (A group call...? That might be fun... I did like talking to Airi and Shizuku...)
Mizuki: (But I...)
Ena: <I just got a reply. Mizuki's tired and going to bed it looks like...>
Airi: <Right. I'd be exhausted too if I had to run around like that...>
Ena: <Yeah... I need to thank you too, Shizuku.>
Shizuku: <No, Mizuki did all the work. I just sort of followed along...>
Airi: <The other people from the tour were so understanding too...>
Ena: <I know, right? I'm glad everyone was so nice about what happened.>
Shizuku: <I was surprised to hear that it was actually Mizuki's friends who came to help us in the end.>
Ena: <Yeah, we're in different classes but go to the same school. I should thank them again if I get a chance to see them.>
Airi: <That'd be great!>
Airi: <But I also feel bad about losing track of why we went there in the first place...>
Shizuku: <Yes, helping Mizuki turned into something much more drastic...>
Ena: <It's okay, really. I'm still glad we went.>
Mizuki: You're safe now and that's what matters most.
Ena: <Today was the first time in a while that I'd seen Mizuki genuinely having a good time...>
Airi: <That's good then.>
Ena: <I learned today that I really do want to know more about what's bothering Mizuki.>
Ena: <I don't know if it's okay for me to keep pushing like this...>
Ena: <But nothing's gonna change unless I do something about it.>
Ena: <Mizuki helped me today, so it's my turn to return the favor.>
Airi: <Ena...>
Ena: <I doubt I'll really learn anything soon, but I want to know more about Mizuki...>
Ena: <I'll keep trying until things do start to actually change...!>
Airi: <Hehe. Looks like Ena's back to her usual self.>
Ena: <Look who's talking. You're the one that told me that not giving up is my best quality, Airi.>
Airi: <Because it is. I really like that part of you, Ena.>
Shizuku: <And feel free to ask us again if there's something you'd like help with. We'll gladly lend you a hand.>
Airi: <Also, how would you guys feel about going out together again?>
Shizuku: <That sounds wonderful! I'm sure it'll be even more fun if both Ena and Mizuki come along!>
Airi: <Mizuki does seem like a good kid. We might just go without you, Ena.>
Ena: <Airi... Shizuku...>
Ena: <But in that case, how does shopping sound? I kind of ruined Mizuki's favorite outfit, so we should probably find something new to replace it.>
Shizuku: <Right. Mizuki's very cute and stylish too, so I'm sure we'll be able to find something good. We'll let you know when our practice schedule is all set.>
Ena: <Okay. Thanks, Shizuku.>
Airi: <*Yawn*... I'm getting pretty sleepy... I think I'll head off to bed...>
Shizuku: <Oh, it is getting late. I'll do the same then.>
Airi: <Bye, you two! And thanks again for today!>
Ena: <Okay, bye.>
Mizuki: You're safe now and that's what matters most.
Ena: (I want Mizuki to smile like that more...)
Ena: (I get that I might start being a nuisance...)
Ena: (But I can't ignore this anymore.)
Ena: (Because Mizuki's my friend...)
Ena: (Because Mizuki's someone I really care about.)
